<span id="freeTextContainer12155320302818738622">Another excellent installment in this impressively rich young adult fantasy series. <br/><br/>Listening to this series on audiobook this summer with my kids (10 and 13) has been a great experience. The story is so detailed and rich, providing entertainment for all three of us. I&apos;m quite invested at this point and looking forward to the final book, <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8069828.The_Crimson_Crown__Seven_Realms___4_' title='The Crimson Crown (Seven Realms, #4) by Cinda Williams Chima' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Crimson Crown</a>. Raisa is a strong and likeable heroine, and the former scoundrel Han continues to mature into an equally endearing male lead.<br/><br/>My daughter&apos;s fa</span>
  <span id="freeText12155320302818738622" style="display:none">Another excellent installment in this impressively rich young adult fantasy series. <br /><br />Listening to this series on audiobook this summer with my kids (10 and 13) has been a great experience. The story is so detailed and rich, providing entertainment for all three of us. I'm quite invested at this point and looking forward to the final book, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/8069828.The_Crimson_Crown__Seven_Realms___4_" title="The Crimson Crown (Seven Realms, #4) by Cinda Williams Chima" rel="nofollow noopener">The Crimson Crown</a>. Raisa is a strong and likeable heroine, and the former scoundrel Han continues to mature into an equally endearing male lead.<br /><br />My daughter's favourite is Amon, the honourable friend and guard, and she continues to hope for an ending that will satisfy her: "I know they have other stuff to worry about, but maybe they will all end up together in a polyamorous marriage."<br /><br />Can I just say how much I love that?</span>
